Description:
A DISPLAY HOUSE THAT IS SIMPLY TOO HARD TO RESIST
Do you remember walking through display homes and thinking "if only..." Well here is your "if only" moment.
Presented for sale in Officer's number one estate is a display home built and maintained by the highly-reputed Simonds Homes.
You're walking distance from public transport, proposed primary school and shops plus only a few minutes and you're on the Monash Freeway.
The house is upgraded at every possibility - from the grand entrance, to the elevated ceilings, to the abundance of light dancing through the house.
- Enjoy the 4 large bedrooms, featuring a master bedroom with large en-suite and walk-in robe;
- Formal living area with shutters separating the main living space;
- Massive kitchen with butler's pantry and waterfall laminate bench tops. And have you noticed the cupboard space?!
- Separate living zone at the rear, perfect for a theatre room;
- Heating and cooling;
- LED lighting throughout with feature pendants to add to the allure.
Need I go on?
- A double car garage with established plumbing facilities;
- Courtyard overlooking landscaped gardens;
- Designer tile flooring;
- Also, did we mention all this is on a 562sqm block? It's unquestionably one of Timbertop's bigger allotments.
The decision isn't really that hard, is it?
